{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "transitlk-api-collection",
    "name": "TransitLK API",
    "description": "TransitLK (SRMSS) REST API collection for integration testing.\n\n## Setup\n1. Start MongoDB and the server: `cd server && npm run dev` (port 5000)\n2. Import this file in Postman: **Import → Upload Files**\n3. Run **Auth → Login (Administrator)** first — the JWT is saved to the `token` collection variable automatically\n4. Run other requests (they use Bearer auth from that token)\n\n## Test accounts (password: `password123`)\n- admin@transitlk.lk — Administrator\n- scheduler@transitlk.lk — Transport Scheduler\n- depot@transitlk.lk — Depot Manager\n- fleet@transitlk.lk — Fleet Manager\n- driver@transitlk.lk — Driver\n- superadmin@transitlk.lk — Superadministrator\n\nSee `docs/Summary.md` for role details.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:5000"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "scheduleId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "routeId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "busId",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "key": "driverId",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{token}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Smoke test — confirms the API server is running. No authentication required."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Server is running', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('Server is running');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (Administrator)",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@transitlk.lk\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Sign in as Administrator. Saves JWT to the `token` collection variable."
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Token returned', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.token);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
